items.content:
Welcome to the Wikiwijs of Unit 6 lesson 2, listening.
Go to goals

Your goals for today are:

  • You can recognise the main topic of a discussion
  • You can understand what is said directly to you
  • You have begun to understand the past simple of irregular verbs and the past simple of to be
  • To have practiced with words regarding nature

Go to past simple irregular

GO TO GOALS CHECK AT THE END OF THE LESSON.

<iframe width="640px" height="480px" src="https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=dfhLkAqv2kOb81_K35a205ENwRphT3hEgO9_sPRvay5UNVBJOU5UMUlLRzFaNDMyR1BQWVpISDFZUy4u&embed=true" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" msallowfullscreen=""/>

Almost all languages have irregular verbs.
Dutch:

Tegenwoordige tijd: Verleden tijd:

Ik slaap Ik sliep

Hij slaapt Hij sliep

content.body:
What is an irregular verb in Dutch?

Het is een

items.content:
In English, it is different but mostly the same.

Present Simple: Past Simple:

I sleep I slept

He sleeps He slept

-

The same happens with other pronouns:

You sleep - You slept

We sleep - We slept

They sleep - They slept

We can see that the entire verb changes form and spelling.

REMEMBER: The verb stays the same with each pronoun.

He slepts IS WRONG.

content.body:
What is the difference with a regular verb in the past simple?

A regular verb is almost always the verb + .
We have to learn the entire irregular verb list by heart.
We have to learn the endings of irregular verbs only.

heading.content: Past Simple Irregular Negative and Question

content.body:
Just like Past Simple regular:

For negative sentences: +

For question sentences: + and a question mark at the end.

For negative sentences: didn't + infinitive (hele werkwoord)
For question sentences: did + infinitive (hele werkwoord)

They right and he wrong.​

We right and she wrong.​
